&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Printed Circuit Board&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;key-points&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Key Points&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;Printed Circuit Board (PCB)&lt;/strong&gt; is a board used to electrically connect and mechanically support electronic components.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;PCBs are made by laminating a non-conductive substrate with layers of copper circuitry.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They are used in almost all electronic devices, including computers, smartphones, and industrial machinery.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Components such as resistors, capacitors, and integrated circuits are soldered onto the PCB to create a functional electronic circuit.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;PCBs can be single-sided, double-sided, or multilayered, depending on the complexity of the electronic circuit.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They provide a compact, reliable, and inexpensive way to interconnect electronic components.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;additional-info&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Additional Information&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;PCBs are designed using specialized computer software to layout the circuitry and component placement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;They can be manufactured using various methods, including etching, milling, and additive printing.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;High-density interconnect (HDI) PCBs are used in advanced electronics to achieve higher performance in a smaller footprint.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The invention of the PCB is attributed to Paul Eisler, who developed the first PCB in 1936 for use in radios.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;<br><br>&lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot;&gt;
